result.execSummary:
The defendant Josalyn L. Riha was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Josalyn L. Riha is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Josalyn L. Riha was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Case called at 2:38 PM.  Defendant Josalyn L. Riha in court with attorney Jane Ellen Bucher.  Jenna L Gill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Bucher has received offer and would like time to review this with her client.  Court in recess at 2:41 PM.  State recalls case at 2:48 PM.  Defendant will resolve case today and pleads No Contest to count 2.  State files Plea Agreement with the Court.  Attorney Bucher files Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form.  Court questions Defendant regarding Plea Questionnaire and Waiver or Rights form.  Court questions Attorney Bucher regarding Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form.  Factual Basis stipulated between parties.  Court is satisfied Defendant enters her plea knowingly, freely, voluntarily, and intelligently and will accept her plea of No Contest and adjudicate her Guilty of Disorderly Conduct.  State will dismiss count 1.  Attorney Bucher makes a statement to the Court.  Court will adopt recommendation of $50.00 fine + costs, 60 DTP-payment plan if needed, Civil Judgment, and will order DNA collection.
Defendant's Demand for Discovery and Inspection
Plea/sentencing hearing on April 18, 2017 at 02:30 pm.

Case called at 11:01 AM.  Defendant Josalyn L. Riha in court with attorney Guy Mason Taylor.  Jenna L Gill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Attorney Taylor informs the Court Defendant will arrange for counseling and parties are investigating Deferred Resolution.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for April 18, 2017 at 02:30 pm.

Case called at 9:32 AM.  Jenna Gill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Josalyn L. Riha in Court.  Special Appearance by Attorney Guy Taylor.  Defendant has received criminal complaint in matter and waives formal reading.  Defendant has been provided with State Public Defender's telephone number and Petition for Waiver of Fees and Costs-Affidavit of Indigency forms.  Court reads charge portion of criminal complaint onto record.  Defendant understands charges.  Court finds probable cause.  Defendant stands mute.  State requests $1,000.00 signature bond with conditions.  Court enters Not Guilty plea.
Defendant shall refrain from violent or abusive threats towards Luther Johnson.
Initial appearance on January 30, 2017 at 09:30 am.

Case called at 9:53 AM.  Defendant Josalyn L. Riha not in court.  Jenna L Gill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Gill informs the Court that Defendant phoned in today and stated she is ill and can not attend hearing.  Initial appearance scheduled for January 30, 2017 at 09:30 am.
